  "title": "Office Manager cum Clients Coordintor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities      </strong></p><p><strong>1.  Office Administration:       </strong>Oversee daily office operations, including managing office supplies, to monitor expiry dates and maintenance of company licenses, and overseeing <a href=\"https://www.mycareersfuture.gov.sg/job/admin/office-manager-5-dayscentral-construction-design-build-industryiso-documentation-tender-processes-regulatory-compliancecrmerp-platforms-linkedcorp-hr-consultancy-dca42fc91efdd4ab89108b57e8a6058b\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ISO documentation</a> and regulatory compliance records.</p><p><strong>2.     Client & Stakeholder Liaison:     </strong>Serve as the primary point of contact for clients, handling enquiries, scheduling project meetings, and maintaining strong professional relationships.</p><p><strong>3.     Project Documentation:   </strong>Assist in the preparation and submission of tender documents, contracts, variation orders, and progress reports,  and all submissions to the authorities.</p><p><strong>4.     Financial Support: </strong>Manage accounting software, process staff expense claims, supplier payments, subcontractor claims and payments and coordinate with the management team for vendor invoicing and monthly progress claims.</p><p><strong>5.     Manpower Coordination: </strong>Monitor site attendance and support HR with foreign worker documentation, permits, and on boarding and all able to manage workers OT and timesheet</p><p><strong>6.     Logistics Management:    </strong>Source quotations from suppliers and subcontractors, and ensure timely delivery of materials to site and to handle projects tools and hardware purchase.<br /></p><p><strong>Work Location: Woodlands Industrial Park (Factory)</strong><br /><strong>Working Hours: 8am to 5.30pm and 6 days a week (Monday to Saturday) </strong></p>",
